28:32.610 --> 28:34.310
These are very sensitive

28:34.310 --> 28:36.950
to a particular level of
light called blue light,

28:36.950 --> 28:39.450
which is approximately 460 nanometers.

28:39.450 --> 28:40.420
Why is that important?

28:40.420 --> 28:42.320
Because when the blue light hits the eye,

28:42.320 --> 28:44.690
it triggers a reaction
in the melanopsin cells,

28:44.690 --> 28:46.010
which sends a signal to the brain

28:46.010 --> 28:48.130
to stop producing melatonin.

28:48.130 --> 28:49.230
Melatonin, if you remember,

28:49.230 --> 28:51.360
