29:46.140 --> 29:47.130
You can shift it a little bit

29:47.130 --> 29:48.410
but it's kind of wired in.

29:48.410 --> 29:50.970
When you wake up, have a glass of water.

29:50.970 --> 29:52.260
Bonus points if you put

29:52.260 --> 29:55.013
about a half a teaspoon of
Himalayan salt in the water

29:55.013 --> 29:57.800
and possibly lemon or lime juice.

29:57.800 --> 29:59.330
If you do that first thing

29:59.330 --> 30:01.340
that actually supports your adrenal glands

30:01.340 --> 30:03.811
and you can have your coffee.

30:03.811 --> 30:06.230
There are a couple of
things that you could eat

30:06.230 --> 30:07.770
in your morning routine.

30:07.770 --> 30:09.830
One practice that I really appreciate

30:09.830 --> 30:11.710
is called intermittent fasting,

30:11.710 --> 30:13.760
which means you don't eat
anything for breakfast

30:13.760 --> 30:14.730
and you have a late lunch,

30:14.730 --> 30:16.270
which gives you an 18 hour window

30:16.270 --> 30:18.530
where your body has nothing going on.

30:18.530 --> 30:19.590
So all of the enzymes

30:19.590 --> 30:20.850
that would have been used for food

30:20.850 --> 30:23.490
can be used for healing
and repair and recovery.

30:23.490 --> 30:25.020
But this is a stressor on the system.

30:25.020 --> 30:27.150
So if you're tired or
you've had a heavy workout,

30:27.150 --> 30:29.165
it's probably not the
right day to do that.

30:29.165 --> 30:32.820
The two things that matter
most in the morning are fat,

30:32.820 --> 30:35.190
the right kinds of fat and protein.

30:35.190 --> 30:36.520
Having a morning protein shake

30:36.520 --> 30:38.184
can be really beneficial for you.

30:38.184 --> 30:40.330
